 INDEXES :- 
 ========= 

  => index is also a db object created to improve query performance.
  => index makes data accessing faster.
  => index in db is similar to index in textbook , in textbook using index a particular topic can
       be located fastly , in db using index a particular record can be located fastly.
  => indexes are created on columns and that column is called index key
  => indexes created on columns 

       1 which are frequently used in where clause
       2 which are frequently used in join condition

       CREATE INDEX <name> ON <tabname>( colname) ; 

 Ex :-  CREATE INDEX I1 ON emp(sal) 

    => after executing above command oracle creates a structure called BTREE 

